Theorem (15.20): - a = (- 1) · a
Proof:
    - a = (- 1) · a
  =⟨ “Additive identity” ⟩
    - a + 0 = (- 1) · a
  =⟨ “Zero of ·” ⟩
    - a + 0 · a = (- 1) · a
  =⟨ “Unary minus” ⟩
    - a + (1 + - 1) · a = (- 1) · a
  =⟨ “Distributivity of · over +” ⟩
    - a + 1 · a + (- 1) · a = (- 1) · a
  =⟨ “Multiplicative identity” ⟩
    - a + a + (- 1) · a = (- 1) · a
  =⟨ “Unary minus” ⟩
    0 + (- 1) · a = (- 1) · a
  =⟨ “Additive identity” ⟩
    (- 1) · a = (- 1) · a — This is “Reflexivity of =”
